ext":"This mode can be useful if the map trajectory is predefined and the user cannot pan"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"freely (e.g. navigation use cases), so that there is a good chance tile packs are already loaded"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the vicinity of the user."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If users can pan freely, this mode is not recommended. Otherwise, panning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will download tile packs instead of using individual tiles. Note that this means that we could first"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"download an individual tile, and then a tile pack that also includes this tile. The individual tile in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the disk cache won’t be used as long as the up-to-date tile pack exists in the cache."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://com.mapbox.MapboxMaps/documentation/MapboxMaps/TileStoreUsageMode":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TileStoreUsageMode","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/TileStoreUsageMode","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/tilestoreusagemode","abstract":[{"text":"Describes tile store usage modes.","type":"text"}],"title":"TileStoreUsageMode","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TileStoreUsageMode","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://com.mapbox.MapboxMaps/documentation/MapboxMaps":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps","url":"\/documentation\/mapboxmaps","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Interactive, thoroughly customizable maps for iOS powered by vector tiles and Metal.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapboxMaps"},"doc://com.mapbox.MapboxMaps/documentation/MapboxMaps/TileStore-API